class Solution {
    public boolean canSortArray(int[] nums) {
        int lastCnt = 0;
        int lastGroupMax = 0;
        int curGroupMax = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            int curCnt = Integer.bitCount(num);
            if (curCnt == lastCnt) {
                curGroupMax = Math.max(curGroupMax, num);
            } else {
                lastCnt = curCnt;
                lastGroupMax = curGroupMax;
                curGroupMax = num;
            }
            if (num < lastGroupMax) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```
In this code, we count the number of set bits in each number and group the numbers according to their number of set bits. We also keep track of the maximum number in each group. If we find a number that is smaller than the maximum number in its group, we return false because it cannot be swapped with any number in its group to sort the array. If we can sort the array, we return true.

