This problem is asking to find the maximum sum of elements in a balanced subsequence of the input array. A balanced subsequence is a subsequence such that the difference between each consecutive element and its index is greater than or equal to one. We can use a binary indexed tree (BIT) to solve this problem. The binary indexed tree is a data structure that can efficiently update elements and calculate prefix sums. The time complexity of the code is O(n log n), where n is the length of the input array.

