class Solution {
public:
    int minimizeMax(vector<int> &nums, int p) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        int left = -1, right = nums.back() - nums[0]; // 开区间
        while (left + 1 < right) { // 开区间
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            int cnt = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < nums.size() - 1; ++i) {
                if (nums[i + 1] - nums[i] <= mid) { // 都选
                    ++cnt;
                    ++i;
                }
            }
            if (cnt >= p) {
                right = mid;
            } else {
                left = mid;
            }
        }
        return right;
    }
};
```

This code first sorts the input array. Then it uses binary search to find the minimum maximum difference. In each iteration of the binary search, it counts the number of pairs of elements where the difference is less than or equal to mid. If the count is greater than or equal to p, the code updates right to mid; otherwise, it updates left to mid. Finally, it returns right as the minimum maximum difference.

